{"title_page": "Thomas & Friends (series 6)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{unreferenced|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox television season \n | season_number = 6\n | bgcolour = #4E5395\n | image = Thomas and Friends DVD Cover - Series 6.jpg\n | image_size = 250px\n | caption = DVD cover art\n | country = United Kingdom \n | network = [[Nick Jr. (UK and Ireland)|Nick Jr.]]<br>[[CITV]]\n | first_aired = {{Start date|df=y|2002|09|16}}\n | last_aired = {{End date|df=y|2002|10|21}}\n | num_episodes = 26\n | episode_list = List of Thomas & Friends episodes\n}}\n'''''[[Thomas the Tank Engine & Friends]]''''' is a [[children's television series]] about the engines and other characters working on the railways of the [[Island of Sodor]], and is based on [[The Railway Series]] books written by the [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]].\n\nThis article lists and details episodes from the 6th series of the show, which was first broadcast in 2002.\n\nThis series was narrated by [[Michael Angelis]] for the UK audiences, who also re-dubbed only 2 episodes for the US audiences, while [[Alec Baldwin]] narrated the episodes for the US audiences, which was also his last series. 6 were re-dubbed by [[Michael Brandon]] for the US audiences. \n\nMost episodes in this series have 1 title: the American titles are shown underneath.\n\nThe first season produced by [[HiT Entertainment]]. Marked the return series after 4 years without new episodes.\n\n==Production==\n\nPhil Fehrle had taken over as producer from [[David Mitton]] and [[Britt Allcroft]], while [[Angus Wright (producer)|Angus Wright]] had been replaced by Allcroft and Peter Urie as executive producers.\n\nThis was the first series to oversee an introduction of a writing staff, since the stories from ''The Railway Series'' had already been adapted. Staff-written stories had been introduced in [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|Series 5]], and this practice remains unchanged since then.\n\nAbi Grant served as script editor for the series. <br/>\nStock Footage: This season had the same theme music as [[Thomas & Friends (series 3)|Seasons 3]], [[Thomas & Friends (series 4)|4]], & [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|5]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background=#4E5395|overall=|season=|title=|titleT=UK title (top)<hr />Main title (middle)<hr />US title (bottom)|director=||writer=|airdate=|episodes=\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=131\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Salty's Secret\n |DirectedBy=[[David Mitton]]\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|16|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Salty (the dockyard diesel) comes to work on Sodor, but is disappointed that he has to work in the center Island Quarry. Bill, Ben, and Mavis soon find out that Salty has absolutely no trouble moving the Troublesome Trucks. One night, Salty goes to get some sea air and Mavis asks him if he really misses the sea. Salty admits that he does. The next day, Sir Topham Hatt visits Salty and sends him to work at Brendam Docks, much to Salty's delight.\n\n* The episode's events were recreated in [[Thomas & Friends (series 17)#ep409|Away from the Sea]].\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=132\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Harvey to the Rescue\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=Jonathan Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|17|df=y}}\n|ShortSummary=Harvey the Crane Engine comes to Sodor on trial, but he is shunned by the other engines due to his unusual appearance, making him miserable. But when Percy has an accident with the Troublesome Trucks, Harvey comes to his rescue, earning respect from the rest of the engines, including Percy.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=133\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=No Sleep for Cranky \n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|18|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Cranky is tired after a hard day's work at the docks, but he must give up a nap to help Salty, Bill, and Ben when they get stranded at the docks due to a shed that he knocked over while trying to drop a set of pipes on Salty for annoying Cranky with his stories.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=134\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=A Bad Day for Harold the Helicopter\"<hr />\"A Bad Day for Harold\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n ||WrittenBy=Simon Nicholson \n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|19|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Harold is boasting that he can take the mail much faster than Percy, and he has a chance to prove himself when Percy gets stuck at a broken signal. However, Harold ends up crash-landing in a nearby haystack after his motor malfunctions, as a result of his insistence that he take the entire mail load in one trip, which is too heavy for him to handle. Fortunately, Percy, feeling sorry for Harold, has him rescued from the haystack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=135\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Elizabeth the Vintage Lorry\"<hr />\"Elizabeth the Vintage Quarry Truck\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|20|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=While taking a heavy special, Thomas breaks his left coupling rods. His crew journeys to a nearby farm looking for a telephone, but instead they find Elizabeth, an old steam quarry truck. Elizabeth acts very rude to Thomas, and after she brings him his replacement coupling rods, she reminds him not to be so careless. Thomas is offended by Elizabeth's rudeness, but he is still very proud of his new coupling rods and is able to resume his journey. Thomas arrives at the docks with his special just in time. When he is about to tell Sir Topham Hatt about Elizabeth, she suddenly arrives. Sir Topham Hatt then reveals that Elizabeth is the first truck he has ever driven. Elizabeth is restored to her former glory, and even Thomas admits that Elizabeth looks grand.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=136\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title= The Fogman\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jonathan Trueman \n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|23|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=In the winter, Cyril the fogman always places detonators on the rails to warn engines of fog, but one winter, Sir Topham Hatt announces that Cyril is to be replaced by a newly invented railway foghorn so that Cyril can get a much-needed break from his job. However, one morning, when the foghorn alerts Percy, the foghorn's loud noise triggers a landslide, smashing the foghorn in the process. As a result, Thomas crashes through the landslide, but Cyril comes to the rescue. Afterward, Sir Topham Hatt declares that Cyril deserves to keep his job, as he is much more reliable than the foghorn.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=137\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Jack Jumps In\n |DirectedBy=Steve Asquith\n |WrittenBy=Jonathan Trueman, Phil Fehrle, and Abi Grant\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas delivers an eager, new front loader named Jack to an excavation site. However, Jack (due to his eagerness to help) has a tendency to try jobs that he is not suited to, which leads to him crashing. Annoyed, Miss Jenny begins to question if Jack is really ready for the pack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=138\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=A Friend in Need\n |DirectedBy=Steve Asquith\n |WrittenBy=Phil Fehrle, Jonathan Trueman, and Abi Grant\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|25|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Jack joins Miss Jenny's crew in excavating the land under an old railway bridge, but Ned the steam shovel is too clumsy to lower his arm enough while passing under the bridge, and by accident, he knocks the important keystones loose. Quickly, Jack holds the bridge up as much as he can, but eventually is unable to hold it any longer, and the entire bridge collapses. However, Miss Jenny is pleased with Jack for his bravery and finally makes him an official member of the pack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=139\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=It's Only Snow\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=James Mason\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|26|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas must find a way to get to a village in time for the holidays when he gets stranded in the snow with Toby after breaking his snowplow, which strikes and demolishes a water tower.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=140\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=Twin Trouble\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=[[Brian Trueman]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|27|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Donald and Douglas have an accident by crashing into a large cart of hay, and afterwards they refuse to work with each other anymore. When Donald is offered a job helping Duck, he eagerly takes the offer, leaving Douglas to work on his own. But soon, the twins start to miss one another. And when Donald inadvertently backs into a ditch due to Duck failing to give him a heads-up in time, Donald realizes how much he and Douglas need each other. Duck, knowing he is too weak to pull Donald out of the ditch, alerts Douglas, and after Douglas rescues Donald, the twins reconcile. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=141\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=The World's Strongest Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|30|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Henry is sent for repairs after an accident, and Sir Topham Hatt, unable to find any other engines available, brings Diesel to the docks to fill in for Henry, much to the displeasure of the other engines. The Troublesome Trucks encourage Diesel to take them all at the same time and prove himself to be the world's strongest engine, and Diesel smugly decides to do so. He then lines up 20 trucks, but forgets to check them to make sure that their brakes are off, and as Diesel pulls on the trucks, he accidentally breaks away, plunges off the wharf, and falls into a barge on the canal. Sir Topham Hatt later sends him away again, while Henry returns to take the trucks, and the other engines, especially Thomas and Percy, are happy to have Henry back. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=142\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Scaredy Engines\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|1|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=It is Halloween, and Edward is telling a scary story about a ghost engine. Sir Topham Hatt assigns Thomas, Duck and Percy to pick up a scrap delivery from the smelters yard and bring it to the docks. Thomas humorously teases Percy for being scared, and when an engine is needed to collect the final load, Duck, feeling sorry for Percy, volunteers Thomas to get back at him. However, as soon as Duck and Percy exit, Thomas gets spooked by the sights and sounds of the smelters, and eventually flees after accidentally setting off an old steam whistle. Percy finds Thomas and forgives him for his teasing and the two friends begin to happily watch the fireworks together. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=143\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=Percy and the Haunted Mine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robyn Charteris\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|2|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy gets spooked when he passes an abandoned mine at night and sees a chimney and a shed sink into the ground. He is even more scared when Donald and Douglas tell him about the \"naughty gnomes\". However, Sir Topham Hatt reveals that the gnomes are simply garden gnomes, and the buildings are just sinking into empty mine shafts.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=144\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=Middle Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Brian Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|3|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Percy goes to the smelters to pick up coal to take to the coaling plant, Arry and Bert play a trick on him by putting him in the middle of the train. This leads to Henry inadvertently and unknowingly pushing Percy onto the loading ramp, and Sir Topham Hatt scolds Percy for this, not believing what Arry and Bert did to him. James is convinced that he can outsmart the diesels, so he does Percy's run to the smelters the next day, but gets made a middle engine by Arry and Bert as well. Sir Topham Hatt sends Percy to pick up James and bring him and his goods train to the docks, much to James' embarrassment.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=145\n |EpisodeNumber2=15\n |Title=James and the <span Style=Color:Red>Red</span> Balloon\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|4|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Thomas delivers a hot air balloon to the airfield, he and James become worried that it could take away their passengers. And at the level crossing, when the balloon crash-lands on James after running out of hot air, he panics and lets off steam, accidentally re-inflating the balloon. His driver praises him, but now James and Thomas are even more worried that the balloon will take their passengers for sure. However, Sir Topham Hatt reveals that the balloon will simply increase the trains' passenger flow, much to the engines' delight.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=146\n |EpisodeNumber2=16\n |Title=Jack Frost\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|7|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=James and Percy have to deliver coal around the Island to prepare for a big freeze, but Percy becomes frightened by the thought of \"Scary Jack Frost\".\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=147\n |EpisodeNumber2=17\n |Title=Gordon Takes a Tumble\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|8|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon does not feel that it would be dignified for an express engine to pull goods trains, but when Salty teases him, Gordon is determined to show him how an express engine pulls trucks. When a signalman inadvertently diverts Gordon onto Thomas' branch line, Gordon begins seeing \"Go slow\" signs, which he ignores. As a result, he derails and gets into a severe accident. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=148\n |EpisodeNumber2=18\n |Title=Percy's <span Style=Color:Chocolate>Chocolate</span> Crunch\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Brian Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|9|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is frustrated that, due to a water shortage, he, along with all the other engines, is restricted one wash-down per day, and so he tries to take several jobs, where he is sure he will not become dirty from the Troublesome Trucks. Percy's driver suggests delivering sugar to the chocolate factory, but when he arrives, he skids on the tracks due to an oil spill, then accidentally crashes through the factory and gets covered in chocolate. However, Percy is delighted when Sir Topham Hatt tells him he will be granted both a wash-down and a new coat of paint as a reward for acknowledging that usefulness comes before cleanliness. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=149\n |EpisodeNumber2=19\n |Title=Harold and the <span style=\"color:DeepSkyBlue\">Sky Blue</span> Bucket\"<hr/>\"Harold and the Blue Bucket\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|10|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= When Sir Topham Hatt arrives at the China Quarry one day, he finds that Ben is sporting damaged buffers. Ben happily goes to the works to get new buffers, while Mavis fills in for him. Bill is jealous that his twin is getting new buffers, but no matter what Mavis tells him, Bill is still ungrateful that he is in fine, working order and wants new buffers, as well. After the Troublesome Trucks nastily mock Bill over his jealousy, Bill finally loses his patience and tries to biff a truck, but is unable to stop himself in time and inadvertently backs straight into an incline, breaking his buffers in the process. Ben (having just returned from the works with his new buffers) comes to help, and Sir Topham Hatt scolds Bill for his misbehavior and tells him to learn the importance of responsibility and reliability before he gets new buffers. Afterwards, Bill compliments Ben on his new buffers, allowing the twins to reconcile.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=150\n |EpisodeNumber2=20\n |Title=Toby Had a Little Lamb\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|11|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=During the winter, Toby is flagged down by a farmer who needs a vet to examine his lambs on the other side of the hill. Duck tries to clear away the snow, but it becomes too thick for him to plough.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=151\n |EpisodeNumber2=21\n |Title=Thomas, Percy and the Squeak\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|14|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas is chosen by Sir Topham Hatt to collect famous Italian opera singer Alicia Botti from the docks, meaning that he gets to be cleaned ahead of Percy, who is displeased by this, as he is a guaranteed connection. After being cleaned, Thomas feels more important then ever, but then starts hearing a squeak, and his driver cannot figure out where it is coming from. However, when he arrives to collect Alicia Botti, she lets out a shrill, prolonged scream (which shatters windows all over the docks) at the sight of a mouse aboard Clarabel, much to Gordon's amusement (as he claimed that she was a [[coloratura]]). Sir Topham Hatt is very embarrassed, and Thomas does not feel important anymore. Percy, just returning from his guaranteed connection, gladly takes over and collects Alicia Botti instead, as she considers him a proper engine for his dirtiness, despite Gordon disapproving of this. At the wash-down later, Thomas apologizes to Percy for acting arrogant and stingy, and allows him to be cleaned first. The two friends reconcile and make a home for the mouse in the sheds, naming her \"Alicia.\"\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=152\n |EpisodeNumber2=22\n |Title=Thomas the Jet Engine\"<hr />\"Thomas and the Jet Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon boasts how much faster he is than the other engines, and Thomas wishes that he could show Gordon up as he goes to collect a jet engine from the docks. When he arrives to pick up the jet engine, Cranky carelessly switches it on with his hook, resulting in the jet engine rocketing Thomas along the main line, surprising the other engines, including Gordon.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=153\n |EpisodeNumber2=23\n |Title=Edward the Very Useful Engine\"<hr />\"Edward the Really Useful Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=David Mitton\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|16|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon believes that Edward is too old, but when Duck gets stuck on Gordon's Hill while pulling a train, and Gordon is stalled behind him, Edward proves Gordon wrong by pushing the long line back to the station.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=154\n |EpisodeNumber2=24\n |Title=Dunkin' Duncan\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Impatient Duncan wants the other engines at the incline to work faster, but they instead stick to the railway rules. After being warned by Rusty and Rheneas that the slate trucks can pay him back, Duncan does not listen and he gets pulled up the incline, resulting in him plunging into a ditch. Sir Topham Hatt tells Duncan that as punishment, he will work at the incline by himself until he learns to be patient and careful.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=155\n |EpisodeNumber2=25\n |Title=Rusty Saves the Day\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|18|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Rheneas and Skarloey's old line is too battered for them to run on, but when the quarry is briefly closed down, Rusty gathers Rheneas, Skarloey, and Elizabeth to help repair and reopen the line.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=156\n |EpisodeNumber2=26\n |Title=Faulty Whistles \n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n ||WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|21|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Peter Sam accidentally gets his whistle knocked off by a branch and is barred from working until he gets a new one (as it would be too dangerous for an engine to run without a whistle), Duncan teases him and boasts that any proper engine has a whistle. To prove his point, Duncan starts whistling loudly, annoying the other engines, Elizabeth, and Terence. Duncan's whistle eventually comes loose while he is delivering a headmaster and an organ, and soon, he blows it off by accident. The headmaster's organ becomes Duncan's temporary whistle until he gets a new one. At first, Duncan is not pleased with this, but when the other engines (including Peter Sam, who has just gotten his new whistle) inform Duncan that he did well without his whistle, Duncan feels better.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Characters==\n\n===Introduced===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Salty|Salty the Dockyard Diesel]] (\"Salty's Secret\")\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Harvey|Harvey the Crane Engine]] (\"Harvey to the Rescue\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Elizabeth|Elizabeth]] (\"Elizabeth the Vintage Lorry\")\n* Cyril (\"The Fogman\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#The Pack|Ms. Jenny Packard]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Jack|Jack]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Oliver|Oliver the Excavator]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Byron|Byron]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Isobella|Isobella]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Kelly|Kelly]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Alfie|Alfie]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Max|Max]] (\"Jack Jumps In\")\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Ned|Ned]] (\"Jack Jumps In\" {{small|(''cameo'')}} / \"A Friend in Need\")\n* Farmer McColl (\"Toby Had a Little Lamb\")\n* Alicia Botti (\"Thomas, Percy and the Squeak\")\n{{div col end}}\n\n===Recurring character cast===\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Thomas the Tank Engine|Thomas]]\n* [[Edward the Blue Engine|Edward]]\n* [[Henry the Green Engine|Henry]]\n* [[Gordon the Big Engine|Gordon]]\n* [[James the Red Engine|James]]\n* [[Percy the Small Engine|Percy]]\n* [[Toby the Tram Engine|Toby]]\n* [[Duck the Great Western Engine|Duck]]\n* [[Donald and Douglas]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Bill and Ben|Bill and Ben]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Diesel|Diesel]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Mavis|Mavis]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Oliver|Oliver the Western Engine]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Stepney|Stepney]]\n* [[Railway engines (Thomas and Friends)#'Arry and Bert|'Arry and Bert]]\n* [[Skarloey]]\n* [[Rheneas]]\n* [[Narrow gauge engines (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Peter Sam|Peter Sam]]\n* [[Rusty the Diesel|Rusty]]\n* [[Duncan (fictional locomotive)|Duncan]]\n* [[Duke]] (music video cameo)\n* [[Annie and Clarabel]] \n* [[Rolling stock (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#Henrietta|Henrietta]] \n* [[Rolling stock (Thomas and Friends)#Troublesome Trucks|Troublesome Trucks]]\n* [[Bertie the Bus|Bertie]]\n* [[Terence the Tractor|Terence]]\n* [[Trevor the Traction Engine|Trevor]]\n* [[Harold the Helicopter|Harold]]\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas the Tank Engine and Friends)#George|George]] (cameo)\n* [[Non-rail vehicles (Thomas and Friends)#Cranky|Cranky]]\n* [[The Fat Controller]]\n* [[Jem Cole]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Thomas}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thomas And Friends (Series 06)}}\n\n[[Category:2002 British television seasons]]\n[[Category:Thomas & Friends seasons]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{unreferenced|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox television season \n | season_number = 6\n | bgcolour = #4E5395\n | image = Thomas and Friends DVD Cover - Series 6.jpg\n | image_size = 250px\n | caption = DVD cover art\n | country = United Kingdom \n | network = [[Nick Jr. (UK and Ireland)|Nick Jr.]]<br>[[CITV]]\n | first_aired = {{Start date|df=y|2002|09|16}}\n | last_aired = {{End date|df=y|2002|10|21}}\n | num_episodes = 26\n | episode_list = List of Thomas & Friends episodes\n}}\n'''''[[Thomas the Tank Engine & Friends]]''''' is a [[children's television series]] about the engines and other characters working on the railways of the [[Island of Sodor]], and is based on [[The Railway Series]] books written by the [[Wilbert Awdry|Rev. W. Awdry]].\n\nThis article lists and details episodes from the 6th series of the show, which was first broadcast in 2002.\n\nThis series was narrated by [[Michael Angelis]] for the UK audiences, who also re-dubbed only 2 episodes for the US audiences, while [[Alec Baldwin]] narrated the episodes for the US audiences, which was also his last series. 6 were re-dubbed by [[Michael Brandon]] for the US audiences. \n\nMost episodes in this series have 1 title: the American titles are shown underneath.\n\nThe first season produced by [[HiT Entertainment]]. Marked the return series after 4 years without new episodes.\n\n==Production==\n\nPhil Fehrle had taken over as producer from [[David Mitton]] and [[Britt Allcroft]], while [[Angus Wright (producer)|Angus Wright]] had been replaced by Allcroft and Peter Urie as executive producers.\n\nThis was the first series to oversee an introduction of a writing staff, since the stories from ''The Railway Series'' had already been adapted. Staff-written stories had been introduced in [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|Series 5]], and this practice remains unchanged since then.\n\nAbi Grant served as script editor for the series. <br/>\nStock Footage: This season had the same theme music as [[Thomas & Friends (series 3)|Seasons 3]], [[Thomas & Friends (series 4)|4]], & [[Thomas & Friends (series 5)|5]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Episodes==\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table\n|background=#4E5395|overall=|season=|title=|titleT=UK title (top)<hr />Main title (middle)<hr />US title (bottom)|director=||writer=|airdate=|episodes=\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=131\n |EpisodeNumber2=1\n |Title=Salty's Secret\n |DirectedBy=[[David Mitton]]\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|16|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Salty (the dockyard diesel) comes to work on Sodor, but is disappointed that he has to work in the center Island Quarry. Bill, Ben, and Mavis soon find out that Salty has absolutely no trouble moving the Troublesome Trucks. One night, Salty goes to get some sea air and Mavis asks him if he really misses the sea. Salty admits that he does. The next day, Sir Topham Hatt visits Salty and sends him to work at Brendam Docks, much to Salty's delight.\n\n* The episode's events were recreated in [[Thomas & Friends (series 17)#ep409|Away from the Sea]].\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=132\n |EpisodeNumber2=2\n |Title=Harvey to the Rescue\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=Jonathan Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|17|df=y}}\n|ShortSummary=Harvey the Crane Engine comes to Sodor on trial, but he is shunned by the other engines due to his unusual appearance, making him miserable. But when Percy has an accident with the Troublesome Trucks, Harvey comes to his rescue, earning respect from the rest of the engines, including Percy.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=133\n |EpisodeNumber2=3\n |Title=No Sleep for Cranky \n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|18|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Cranky is tired after a hard day's work at the docks, but he must give up a nap to help Salty, Bill, and Ben when they get stranded at the docks due to a shed that he knocked over while trying to drop a set of pipes on Salty for annoying Cranky with his stories.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=134\n |EpisodeNumber2=4\n |Title=A Bad Day for Harold the Helicopter\"<hr />\"A Bad Day for Harold\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n ||WrittenBy=Simon Nicholson \n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|19|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Harold is boasting that he can take the mail much faster than Percy, and he has a chance to prove himself when Percy gets stuck at a broken signal. However, Harold ends up crash-landing in a nearby haystack after his motor malfunctions, as a result of his insistence that he take the entire mail load in one trip, which is too heavy for him to handle. Fortunately, Percy, feeling sorry for Harold, has him rescued from the haystack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=135\n |EpisodeNumber2=5\n |Title=Elizabeth the Vintage Lorry\"<hr />\"Elizabeth the Vintage Quarry Truck\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|20|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=While taking a heavy special, Thomas breaks his left coupling rods. His crew journeys to a nearby farm looking for a telephone, but instead they find Elizabeth, an old steam quarry truck. Elizabeth acts very rude to Thomas, and after she brings him his replacement coupling rods, she reminds him not to be so careless. Thomas is offended by Elizabeth's rudeness, but he is still very proud of his new coupling rods and is able to resume his journey. Thomas arrives at the docks with his special just in time. When he is about to tell Sir Topham Hatt about Elizabeth, she suddenly arrives. Sir Topham Hatt then reveals that Elizabeth is the first truck he has ever driven. Elizabeth is restored to her former glory, and even Thomas admits that Elizabeth looks grand.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=136\n |EpisodeNumber2=6\n |Title= The Fogman\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jonathan Trueman \n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|23|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=In the winter, Cyril the fogman always places detonators on the rails to warn engines of fog, but one winter, Sir Topham Hatt announces that Cyril is to be replaced by a newly invented railway foghorn so that Cyril can get a much-needed break from his job. However, one morning, when the foghorn alerts Percy, the foghorn's loud noise triggers a landslide, smashing the foghorn in the process. As a result, Thomas crashes through the landslide, but Cyril comes to the rescue. Afterward, Sir Topham Hatt declares that Cyril deserves to keep his job, as he is much more reliable than the foghorn.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=137\n |EpisodeNumber2=7\n |Title=Jack Jumps In\n |DirectedBy=Steve Asquith\n |WrittenBy=Jonathan Trueman, Phil Fehrle, and Abi Grant\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|24|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas delivers an eager, new front loader named Jack to an excavation site. However, Jack (due to his eagerness to help) has a tendency to try jobs that he is not suited to, which leads to him crashing. Annoyed, Miss Jenny begins to question if Jack is really ready for the pack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=138\n |EpisodeNumber2=8\n |Title=A Friend in Need\n |DirectedBy=Steve Asquith\n |WrittenBy=Phil Fehrle, Jonathan Trueman, and Abi Grant\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|25|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Jack joins Miss Jenny's crew in excavating the land under an old railway bridge, but Ned the steam shovel is too clumsy to lower his arm enough while passing under the bridge, and by accident, he knocks the important keystones loose. Quickly, Jack holds the bridge up as much as he can, but eventually is unable to hold it any longer, and the entire bridge collapses. However, Miss Jenny is pleased with Jack for his bravery and finally makes him an official member of the pack.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=139\n |EpisodeNumber2=9\n |Title=It's Only Snow\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=James Mason\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|26|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas must find a way to get to a village in time for the holidays when he gets stranded in the snow with Toby after breaking his snowplow, which strikes and demolishes a water tower.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=140\n |EpisodeNumber2=10\n |Title=Twin Trouble\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=[[Brian Trueman]]\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|27|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Donald and Douglas have an accident by crashing into a large cart of hay, and afterwards they refuse to work with each other anymore. When Donald is offered a job helping Duck, he eagerly takes the offer, leaving Douglas to work on his own. But soon, the twins start to miss one another. And when Donald inadvertently backs into a ditch due to Duck failing to give him a heads-up in time, Donald realizes how much he and Douglas need each other. Duck, knowing he is too weak to pull Donald out of the ditch, alerts Douglas, and after Douglas rescues Donald, the twins reconcile. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=141\n |EpisodeNumber2=11\n |Title=The World's Strongest Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|9|30|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Henry is sent for repairs after an accident, and Sir Topham Hatt, unable to find any other engines available, brings Diesel to the docks to fill in for Henry, much to the displeasure of the other engines. The Troublesome Trucks encourage Diesel to take them all at the same time and prove himself to be the world's strongest engine, and Diesel smugly decides to do so. He then lines up 20 trucks, but forgets to check them to make sure that their brakes are off, and as Diesel pulls on the trucks, he accidentally breaks away, plunges off the wharf, and falls into a barge on the canal. Sir Topham Hatt later sends him away again, while Henry returns to take the trucks, and the other engines, especially Thomas and Percy, are happy to have Henry back. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=142\n |EpisodeNumber2=12\n |Title=Scaredy Engines\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|1|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=It is Halloween, and Edward is telling a scary story about a ghost engine. Sir Topham Hatt assigns Thomas, Duck and Percy to pick up a scrap delivery from the smelters yard and bring it to the docks. Thomas humorously teases Percy for being scared, and when an engine is needed to collect the final load, Duck, feeling sorry for Percy, volunteers Thomas to get back at him. However, as soon as Duck and Percy exit, Thomas gets spooked by the sights and sounds of the smelters, and eventually flees after accidentally setting off an old steam whistle. Percy finds Thomas and forgives him for his teasing and the two friends begin to happily watch the fireworks together. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=143\n |EpisodeNumber2=13\n |Title=Percy and the Haunted Mine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robyn Charteris\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|2|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy gets spooked when he passes an abandoned mine at night and sees a chimney and a shed sink into the ground. He is even more scared when Donald and Douglas tell him about the \"naughty gnomes\". However, Sir Topham Hatt reveals that the gnomes are simply garden gnomes, and the buildings are just sinking into empty mine shafts.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=144\n |EpisodeNumber2=14\n |Title=Middle Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Brian Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|3|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Percy goes to the smelters to pick up coal to take to the coaling plant, Arry and Bert play a trick on him by putting him in the middle of the train. This leads to Henry inadvertently and unknowingly pushing Percy onto the loading ramp, and Sir Topham Hatt scolds Percy for this, not believing what Arry and Bert did to him. James is convinced that he can outsmart the diesels, so he does Percy's run to the smelters the next day, but gets made a middle engine by Arry and Bert as well. Sir Topham Hatt sends Percy to pick up James and bring him and his goods train to the docks, much to James' embarrassment.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=145\n |EpisodeNumber2=15\n |Title=James and the <span Style=Color:Red>Red</span> Balloon\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |Aux2=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|4|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Thomas delivers a hot air balloon to the airfield, he and James become worried that it could take away their passengers. And at the level crossing, when the balloon crash-lands on James after running out of hot air, he panics and lets off steam, accidentally re-inflating the balloon. His driver praises him, but now James and Thomas are even more worried that the balloon will take their passengers for sure. However, Sir Topham Hatt reveals that the balloon will simply increase the trains' passenger flow, much to the engines' delight.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=146\n |EpisodeNumber2=16\n |Title=Jack Frost\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|7|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=James and Percy have to deliver coal around the Island to prepare for a big freeze, but Percy becomes frightened by the thought of \"Scary Jack Frost\".\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=147\n |EpisodeNumber2=17\n |Title=Gordon Takes a Tumble\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Robin Kingsland\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|8|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon does not feel that it would be dignified for an express engine to pull goods trains, but when Salty teases him, Gordon is determined to show him how an express engine pulls trucks. When a signalman inadvertently diverts Gordon onto Thomas' branch line, Gordon begins seeing \"Go slow\" signs, which he ignores. As a result, he derails and gets into a severe accident. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=148\n |EpisodeNumber2=18\n |Title=Percy's <span Style=Color:Chocolate>Chocolate</span> Crunch\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Brian Trueman\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|9|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Percy is frustrated that, due to a water shortage, he, along with all the other engines, is restricted one wash-down per day, and so he tries to take several jobs, where he is sure he will not become dirty from the Troublesome Trucks. Percy's driver suggests delivering sugar to the chocolate factory, but when he arrives, he skids on the tracks due to an oil spill, then accidentally crashes through the factory and gets covered in chocolate. However, Percy is delighted when Sir Topham Hatt tells him he will be granted both a wash-down and a new coat of paint as a reward for acknowledging that usefulness comes before cleanliness. \n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=149\n |EpisodeNumber2=19\n |Title=Buffer Bother\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|10|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary= When Sir Topham Hatt arrives at the China Quarry one day, he finds that Ben is sporting damaged buffers. Ben happily goes to the works to get new buffers, while Mavis fills in for him. Bill is jealous that his twin is getting new buffers, but no matter what Mavis tells him, Bill is still ungrateful that he is in fine, working order and wants new buffers, as well. After the Troublesome Trucks nastily mock Bill over his jealousy, Bill finally loses his patience and tries to biff a truck, but is unable to stop himself in time and inadvertently backs straight into an incline, breaking his buffers in the process. Ben (having just returned from the works with his new buffers) comes to help, and Sir Topham Hatt scolds Bill for his misbehavior and tells him to learn the importance of responsibility and reliability before he gets new buffers. Afterwards, Bill compliments Ben on his new buffers, allowing the twins to reconcile.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=150\n |EpisodeNumber2=20\n |Title=Toby Had a Little Lamb\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|11|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=During the winter, Toby is flagged down by a farmer who needs a vet to examine his lambs on the other side of the hill. Duck tries to clear away the snow, but it becomes too thick for him to plough.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=151\n |EpisodeNumber2=21\n |Title=Thomas, Percy and the Squeak\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|14|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Thomas is chosen by Sir Topham Hatt to collect famous Italian opera singer Alicia Botti from the docks, meaning that he gets to be cleaned ahead of Percy, who is displeased by this, as he is a guaranteed connection. After being cleaned, Thomas feels more important then ever, but then starts hearing a squeak, and his driver cannot figure out where it is coming from. However, when he arrives to collect Alicia Botti, she lets out a shrill, prolonged scream (which shatters windows all over the docks) at the sight of a mouse aboard Clarabel, much to Gordon's amusement (as he claimed that she was a [[coloratura]]). Sir Topham Hatt is very embarrassed, and Thomas does not feel important anymore. Percy, just returning from his guaranteed connection, gladly takes over and collects Alicia Botti instead, as she considers him a proper engine for his dirtiness, despite Gordon disapproving of this. At the wash-down later, Thomas apologizes to Percy for acting arrogant and stingy, and allows him to be cleaned first. The two friends reconcile and make a home for the mouse in the sheds, naming her \"Alicia.\"\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=152\n |EpisodeNumber2=22\n |Title=Thomas the Jet Engine\"<hr />\"Thomas and the Jet Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|15|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon boasts how much faster he is than the other engines, and Thomas wishes that he could show Gordon up as he goes to collect a jet engine from the docks. When he arrives to pick up the jet engine, Cranky carelessly switches it on with his hook, resulting in the jet engine rocketing Thomas along the main line, surprising the other engines, including Gordon.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=153\n |EpisodeNumber2=23\n |Title=Edward the Very Useful Engine\"<hr />\"Edward the Really Useful Engine\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=David Mitton\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|16|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Gordon believes that Edward is too old, but when Duck gets stuck on Gordon's Hill while pulling a train, and Gordon is stalled behind him, Edward proves Gordon wrong by pushing the long line back to the station.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=154\n |EpisodeNumber2=24\n |Title=Dunkin' Duncan\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Jenny McDade\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|17|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Impatient Duncan wants the other engines at the incline to work faster, but they instead stick to the railway rules. After being warned by Rusty and Rheneas that the slate trucks can pay him back, Duncan does not listen and he gets pulled up the incline, resulting in him plunging into a ditch. Sir Topham Hatt tells Duncan that as punishment, he will work at the incline by himself until he learns to be patient and careful.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=155\n |EpisodeNumber2=25\n |Title=Rusty Saves the Day\n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n |WrittenBy=Paul Larson\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|18|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=Rheneas and Skarloey's old line is too battered for them to run on, but when the quarry is briefly closed down, Rusty gathers Rheneas, Skarloey, and Elizabeth to help repair and reopen the line.\n |LineColor=4E5395\n}}\n {{Episode list/sublist|Thomas & Friends (series 6)\n |EpisodeNumber=156\n |EpisodeNumber2=26\n |Title=Faulty Whistles \n |DirectedBy=David Mitton\n ||WrittenBy=Ross Hastings\n |OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2002|10|21|df=y}}\n |ShortSummary=When Peter Sam accidentally gets his whistle knocked off by a branch and is barred from working until he gets a new one (as it would be too dangerous for an engine to run without a whistle), Duncan teases him and boasts that any proper engine has a whistle. To prove his point, Duncan starts whistling loudly, annoying the other engines, Elizabeth, and Terence. Duncan's whistle eventually comes loose while he is delivering a headmaster and an organ, and soon, he blows it off by accident. The headmaster's organ becomes Duncan's temporary whistle until he gets a new one. At first, Duncan is not pleased with this, but when the other engines (including Peter Sam, who has just gotten his new whistle) inform Duncan that he did well without his whistle, Duncan feels better.\n 